        {
            "text": "membranes. Further studies demonstrated that SCG can inhibit degranulation and the release of cytokines and inflammatory mediators from MCs (16) . Interestingly, it has been investigated the role of SCG as protective factor during the initial process of influenza virus infection and the possible mechanism behind any such effects in mouse model. It has been shown that SCG can improve the mouse survival and respiratory pathological changes. Although viral replication was not inhibited, SCG could regulate the expressions of IL-6, TNF-\u03b1, TLR3, and TRIF to alleviate the pathological injury to the nose, trachea, and lungs by reducing the inflammatory response (17) .",
            "cite_spans": [
