        "FIGREF2": {
            "text": "PEA and SCG are able to inhibit degranulation of Mast cells and the release of proinflammatory mediators (i.e. caspase-1). PEA through indirect activation of CB2 receptors. Several mechanisms have been proposed for SCG. PEA: palmitoylethanolamide; SCG: sodium cromoglycate.",
